{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/tlsconnectionsignalname\/notify"]}],"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"abstract":[{"text":"The notify signal is emitted on an object when one of its properties has","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"its value set through ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_set_property()"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_object_set()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", et al."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"case","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"notify","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that getting this signal doesn’t itself guarantee that the value of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the property has actually changed. When it is emitted is determined by the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"derived GObject class. If the implementor did not create the property with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[explicit_notify](\/\/documentation\/gobject\/explicit_notify, then any call to "},{"code":"g_object_set_property()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" results"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"notify"},{"text":" being emitted, even if the new value is the same as the old.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If they did pass [explicit_notify](\/\/documentation\/gobject\/explicit_notify, then this signal is emitted only"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"when they explicitly call ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_notify()"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_notify_by_pspec()"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and common practice is to do that only when the value has actually changed.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This signal is typically used to obtain change notification for a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"single property, by specifying the property name as a detail in the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_signal_connect()"},{"type":"text","text":" call, like this:"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"(C Language Example):"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"C","type":"codeListing","code":["g_signal_connect (text_view->buffer, \"notify::paste-target-list\",","                  G_CALLBACK (gtk_text_view_target_list_notify),","                  text_view)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is important to note that you must use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"#class@GObject.ParamSpec#parameter-names","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" as","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"detail strings for the notify signal.","type":"text"}]}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSConnectionSignalName"]]},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Case","symbolKind":"case","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"case","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"notify"}],"modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"externalID":"s:3GIO23TLSConnectionSignalNameO6notifyyA2CmF","title":"TLSConnectionSignalName.notify"},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSConnectionSignalName\/notify","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/TLSConnectionSignalName/notify":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSConnectionSignalName\/notify","fragments":[{"text":"case","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"iden